      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i see that. but when people talk about the \"failures,\" do historians usually see those as actual flaws in the UN system itself, or is it more that the UN just isn't built to handle how much the world has changed? like, is the criticism that the structure is broken, or just that global politics is too messy for any organization to work?",
